docs.abstract: The W.N.B.A. star took time away from basketball to help Irons overturn his conviction.
docs.snippet: The W.N.B.A. star took time away from basketball to help Irons overturn his conviction.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jonathan Irons, whose bid for freedom from a 50-year prison sentence was embraced and pushed by the W.N.B.A. star Maya Moore, walked out of a Missouri penitentiary on Wednesday, nearly four months after a judge overturned his conviction on charges of burglary and assault.

headline.main: Jonathan Irons, Helped by W.N.B.A. Star Maya Moore, Freed From Prison
headline.print_headline: He Walks Free After an Assist From a W.N.B.A. Star

docs.lead_paragraph: I have always believed that fashion is the window to the soul. As a Black disabled woman with cerebral palsy, a neurological disorder that affects movement on the right side of my body, I have gone through what I call the stages of fashion grief.
